Top Stories (January 31)

CHENEY TO LEAD ADMINISTRATION'S SPECIAL ENERGY TASK FORCE
Describing California as the poster child for the electricity woes the nation 
could face, President Bush on Monday commissioned a special energy task force 
to study how to cope with rising prices and increase domestic energy 
production.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMAKRT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/knightri
dder/2001/01/31/krtbn/0000-0468-SJ-ENERGY-PANEL

CALIFORNIA POWER BILL WITH RATE HIKE CLAUSE GETS BACKING
Utility representatives and consumer advocates Tuesday expressed qualified 
support for a state power-buying bill that says rates could increase based on 
how much power consumers use.
http://199.97.97.79/IMDS%PMADJN0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/djn/2001/
01/31/eng-djn/eng-djn_030038_66_5025933156721

POWER FIRMS MAY POUR BILLIONS INTO QUICK-START PLANTS IN WEST VIRGINIA
Two half-built power-line towers reach toward an AEP high-voltage line that 
crosses the Big Sandy River near the Aristech Chemical Corp. plant here in 
Wayne County.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMAKRT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/knightri
dder/2001/01/31/krtbn/0000-0543-WV-POWER

HOUSTON-BASED ENRON PLANS BAHAMAS-FLORIDA NATURAL GAS PIPELINE
Add a 90-mile natural gas pipeline from the Bahamas to the list of projects 
that Texas-based energy giant Enron Corp. is pursuing for electricity-hungry 
Florida.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMAKRT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/knightri
dder/2001/01/31/krtbn/0000-0191-FL-ENRON

